% if: executable(curl)

curl - Common Options

Transfer data with [prgm]curl[/prgm].

$ [prgm]curl[/prgm] [arg]-sLo[/arg] [arg-value]file.zip[/arg-value] [arg-value]https://example.com/file.zip[/arg-value]

Output

  [arg]-o[/arg] [arg-value]file[/arg-value]           save to named file
  [arg]-O[/arg]                save with remote filename
  [arg]-s[/arg]                silent — no progress output
  [arg]-v[/arg]                verbose — show request and response headers

Request

  [arg]-L[/arg]                follow redirects
  [arg]-I[/arg]                HEAD request (headers only)
  [arg]-X[/arg] [arg-value]METHOD[/arg-value]         override HTTP method
  [arg]-H[/arg] [arg-value]"Header: val"[/arg-value]  set a request header
